com.itko.lisa.remote.transactions

Class TransactionFrame

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.itko.lisa.remote.transactions.TransactionFrame
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class TransactionFrame
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    This is the POJO used to encapsulate all the data about an intercepted method call. It is called a frame by analogy with a stack frame. It is the core data class of Pathfinder and all its extensions. It has data about the class, method, arguments, return value, etc... where it was generated.
    It is hierarchical by nature, i.e. it has a parent frame (which may be null if this is a root frame) and a (possibly empty) collection of children, so we receive a frame, we actually receive a call tree, which we also refer to as a transaction. Multiple partial transactions may be assembled or stitched by the broker using the frameId/parentId fields.
